        body: 'Ready mix concrete, known as zege tayari in Swahili, is concrete that is precisely manufactured at a central batching plant and delivered to construction sites in a freshly mixed state. Unlike traditional site-mixed concrete where cement, sand, aggregate and water are combined on location using a concrete mixer, ready mix concrete is produced under strict quality-controlled conditions using computerised batching systems. This ensures each load meets exactly the specified mix design, grade and consistency required for the project. In Tanzania, ready mix concrete has become increasingly popular for both residential and commercial projects, particularly in Dar es Salaam where quality assurance and construction speed are paramount.'
